          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The lock is implemented by an entry (such as a file or directory) in the file system. For multiple applications to use an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdistributedlock",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " object to coordinate their activities, the lock must be writable on a file system accessible to all hosts on which the applications might be running.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdistributedlock/1412293-try",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method to attempt to acquire a lock. You should generally use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdistributedlock/1417238-unlock",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method to release the lock rather than ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdistributedlock/1413425-break",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdistributedlock",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " doesn’t conform to the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nslocking",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " protocol, nor does it have a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "lock",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " method. The protocol’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nslocking/1416318-lock",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method is intended to block the execution of the thread until successful. For an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdistributedlock",
              "isActive": false,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " object, this could mean polling the file system at some predetermined rate. A better solution is to provide the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsdistributedlock/1412293-try",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method and let you determine the polling frequency that makes sense for your application.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
